  "status": "active",
  "description": "The Spirarchy's keeper of the founding lie; author of the cruelest clean solution.",
  "narrative": "Roak, Recensor's line, weather - the line that has kept the founding secret for a thousand years. Velute knows what the founders did to Suruveil and believes, with real conviction, that a thousand years of order vindicates the silence. She is right about panic; let her say it well. GM ARC (Act 5): she will offer the Settling Right - requisition the Spindles, ten thousand unrecorded lungs the Record would never miss, to wake the Unsung. The offer comes in a quiet room, politely, with tea. She will also trade: truth-management for genuine help containing panic. Disposition track Spirarchy: starts Hostile.",
